\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Flat 101, Dora House. St Johns Wood Rod, NW8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 And you are a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Can you remember the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. 1923.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Kingsgate Street, Holborn. Lincolns Inns Fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many years did you live in Kingsgate Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - I should say - I lost mother when I was seven. My mother died when I was seven. And - from there - I went to Newmarke
t to live with my Uncle Fred, that's got two houses - the racecourse there, because - mother died and dad had three business running, and he couldn't - look after me so I had to have a nanny - down at Newmarket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How long did you live in Newmarket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh I was there two years. Two years. I fretted and I had to come back. To my father. So he - got a lady in to look after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So where did you live then, in Kingsgate Street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, I didn't live in Kingsgate Street then - father moved to - now 
what was the first move he had - Red Lion Street, Holborn. And - he had a shop there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of shop was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
A greengrocers and sweet shop. And - well then he was there for about - oh I suppose nine years. Then he had another shop in - Red Lion Street. He was there for about ten years. And then he had another shop in Ann Court, Hoborn. All in Holborn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you live above the shops in these places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Yes, we lived above the shop, we had the whole top part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So why did he make these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well to - you see the shop got bigger, dad got more money like, and as the money grew - expanded the shops and he had to employ more men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where would you be living in 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, 1911, just a minute, 1911 - I should be living in
 Judge Street. Judge Street. Jud isn't it, that's at - in Euston Road. Now let's see, what number was it? I think it was number forty-nine. Dad had a shop in there, Jud Street,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did the shops get progressively bigger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Bigger, yes, each time. Well
 then - my sister - I had a sister - she lived with us and she had five kiddies, and - this is all before - 1914 war. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 She was a lot older than you was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. She was - she was thirty-four when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You say she had five children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes. Well - I was young you see, she - her hubby went to the war, and she came to stay with my father. And - her hubby was in the - went to join up in the Army, and - my father being Catholic you see - my sister - slipped and - a baby she was carr
ying and - baby - was born and everything you know all before the police could get there or anything, 'cos she slipped you see and she thought it was the - warning - for air raid - and it just begin - when the beginning of the war - like just before - jus
t
 the starting of the war, and - she thought it was air raid and she went to run down the stairs to get the children - and - that was the sign to say peace had been - the war had just been proclaimed - in 1914, you see, so - 'course father - pardon, she lo
s
t the baby, yes, and father had the five kiddies on his hands and - having the business he didn't know what to do so he put them into a convent - for so long. And - he couldn't rest. He got them out the convent. And - my father bought up the children - hi
mself like with a lady comes in an I used to help - with
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was your sister still living there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. She died with the baby, yes, she died - she lived three hours - after that we had the police and all that and the doctor and all that and the b
aby died with her and - 'course we buried her, and - my brother-in-law, he - as I say he was in the Army, and - we got him home for the funeral, and he went back the Army and - he came home on leave and he died, a twelve months - after my sister. He died 
of dropsey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So the five children were orphans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 We had the five children, yes, and of course my father brought them up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you have any other brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. I had - a brother Jack. He went in the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was he older or younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How much older was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh he was about - oh - he was about - six year older than me. And - then - he went to the war, and he was wounded, and he came home and he had gangrene set into the wounds, and they sent hi
m to University Hospital, and there he died. And - had a big military funeral for him in - Harrow Road, Binney Street Big military funeral he had. Well then I had another brother, he went to the war. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was he older as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, he was younge
r, he was three years - oh he was three years older than me if that's what you mean. Yes, three years older than me. And - he was a prisoner of war - for two years, and he came home and - got married and - a family of his own, and - of course he was - lik
e his own boss, he had a house at Kenton, Newham Way, and - he got married and had - brought a family up and he died. So that only left me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So you just had your two brothers and one sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 That's right. And myself. And I'm - I'm the last - the 
last one left. That's right, I'm the only one. Well after that - as I say the children got bigger. Dad give up - his business, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When did he give up his business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 The shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When did he give it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well when he began to fall ill a
 bit. He felt queer and he found that - that the - oh I don't know, something or the other, whether it was the worry of the children or not I don't know that brought on this illness. Well anyway - he was taken very ill, and we lived in - we lived in Jud S
treet the same time, in Jud Street. And - the war was on then - no, after - this is - do you want this before or after? Well my father died - in - he died in - 194 - 15, 16. 1917 he died. My father. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So that left you looking after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
That's right, I brought - five children up. And - I used to get help of course with the lady. And - well then they - some of them got big enough and they got boyfriends, and they got married and they all live at Jud Street, still I think in the buildin
gs there. And of course they got married and they've got grandchildren as well now, but as regards to myself I - picked up with my hubby - and - I met him - when I was about - mm, sixteen - eighteen. I was engaged for - I think twenty - two years, three y
ears, I got married when I was twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When did you first meet your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh now I've got to think now - at a dance. At - where were we dancing? It wasn't Lyceum, it wasn't the Lyceum, it was - oh - \{BLANK\} harrow Road. So there, we went t
o a dance, and I met him in there and - got together and - got engaged. And I got married as I say in 1923. Well - yes. Well then of course I - I was married a twelve month and - my eldest son was born in 19 - 24. And then - I had another son in five - 26
. And I only had the two children. That's all. Hubby was a printer. Worked there fifty years, one job. Never - never ill a day. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was your father always in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. No. He used to - now and again he used to visit the shops. He used to l
eave the men - in charge, too look after the shops.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many did he have in all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Three. Three shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did he start off as?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Just as a greengrocers and then - he had a - the other shop was greengrocer one side, sweet shop the other side. You see, and he carried on like that 'til he was taken bad and had to give them up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 As far as you can remember he was always a shop owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes, yes, always. Well my - as I say my - his father was a Captain in the Royal Navy. And - Capt
ain Fisher, he went down on - with the ship. I've got that on mother's marriage lines there, my mother's marriage lines. And - I left school in 1915, and that is my leaving certificate all in bits. Oh - it's all in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You say your mother and father married in 1900?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
1900, my mother and father I - like this mother and father. Well previous to that - my mother had been married, and she had two sons - by the first husband. And my father met my mother - he'd been married before and had my sister. So we
 were like - half - half brother and sister. Well then - when mum and dad got married they had me. I was the only one they had. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Their previous partners died did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Oh yes. Grandfather died - my grandfather, Captain in the Royal Nav
y, he died - oh - he must have been about five or six years previous to that. He was on his ship when he - his ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where did your father come from? Was it London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes. Come from London. Of course all his people - he's got a brother at - Newmarket, he had a sis - a sister at Fulham. Got a shop business. And - and the other brother died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - yes, yes, he used to go and visit. Of course when I was a child they used to take me with them, and - used to go down in the car like, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How far is Newmarket, about fifty miles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh - the racing - oh yes, a long way, you had to go by car. We never used to go by train or anything because dad had the car you see that could run it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 A sort of actual engine driven car?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes, yes. And - oh yes - we had everything - I had everything - you know, that. I never knew what to rough it was. Those days, never at all. Always had plenty and - I always attended church, always go dancing and - theatres. Drur
y Lane, the Opera House and all that my father used to take me when I was quite a child. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You say you were only seven when your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well, she must have come from Newmarket I think where her 
brother was. 'Cos she had a brother there you see, and now I can't quite - remember - her brother I know she did have a brother - but I never went to - into the details of that at all. Never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 She didn't work. No. No. She never went to work. No, she never went to work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many rooms were in the house - which is the house you can remember best?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh there was about six in each house we went to. Six rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What was the distribution? What were they used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh bedrooms, sitting room, kitchen. And - that's all I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many bedrooms would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well, there used to be - about two because brothers was out in war. I should imagine about - three bedrooms. Kitchen, 'cos those days they never
 used to have a sitting room. Er - kitchen and bathroom. And yes, we did, used to have a sitting room. Must have been about eight rooms I should imagine, not six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So you had a bathroom as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Pardon? Oh yes, yes, yes, we had a bathroom, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When would bathnight be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Friday night. Most of the time. Always Friday night we used to take it in turns - having a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many of you were living in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well as I say, me two brothers were in the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 They weren't at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
They weren't there, but we still had the - the amount of rooms in the place. And me sister -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When you were little they'd still be around wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes, they were around - oh when I was a little girl, yes, they were around 
- well I suppose see - we had a - we never had less than a six roomed house. Never. And - we used to use the - you know, those days they never used to have the - bathrooms, we used to have the long tin baths - that we used to get out and fill with the hot
 water - you know, in a - big tank - we used to have in the - used to be in the toilet where - the toilet - was divisioned - a - away from where we used to have the bath. So that's how that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 It was a separate room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Separate room, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was that off the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Off the kitchen. Mm. Off the kitchen and toilet was - not like the toilet is here. You've got your bathroom in the toilet, we never used to have that, we used to have the - the bathroom away from the - toilet, divided,
 whether my father had it done himself specially I couldn't say. Wouldn't know. But - that's as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What would be the sleeping arrangements of the whole house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Sleeping and - at the shop. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many would there be in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well I'll tell you, when the broth - my brothers used to come home there used to be - my sister -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How much older than you was she?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh she was thirty-four when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 In 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How much older now, 1914 - she'd have been - I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Twenty-one when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 That's right. Twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was she living at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, no, oh no, she had her own place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So there was only your two brothers and yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 And myself. That's right. That's rig
ht, yes. My sister had a - a house in - New North Street, Holborn. Because - as I say her hubby used to go to the war and - used to come home you know now and again but - we always had a house, both families, never been in a flat, this is the first flat I
'
ve ever been in in my life. I never thought I could stomach always having a house, but - still it's rather nice, you know, you get to mix with people here and - you enjoy yourself and you have plenty of - I mean - pardon? Yes, it is very nice, the rent's 
dear but there again - I mean - if you didn't have the money you could always go and get help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you ever have any relatives living in the house in Jud Street or wherever?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No. No, we never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You didn't have any lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did your mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes, we used to have a woman - I couldn't tell you where she is though now. I don't know where she - yes, we used to have a woman -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did she live in or live out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, out. Used to live out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How often would she come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
She used to come in three times a week. That would be on a Saturday - on a Wednesday, and I think a Monday. Three times a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of things did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well she did bedrooms, kitchens - was
hing up. Each day individually she used to make it - you know, a day for - whatever she'd do. She used to leave the bedrooms I think until a Wed - a Friday, bedrooms. No - that's - telling fibs. Used to do the kitchen on a Friday. That's right. Bedrooms o
n the Wednesday. And Mondays she used to do - things in general, you know, like - help do for me or - help perhaps mother do things and then she used to tell her what to do - and all that and she used to do it. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What about washing, did you do the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh mother used to send that out, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where would she send that to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh the laun - nearest laundry, whatever - wherever we were. We were mostly - we were mostly - in the shop in - Red Lion Street, near Great Ormond Stre
et Hospital. Near there, that's where we mostly used to be, but the other shops were run by - managers like for my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Who was this woman who used to come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 I couldn't tell you. No. No. Couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did she call you and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
My name was Virginia and she used to call me Virginia, and my mother's name was Caroline. But she used to call her as I say - Mrs Fisher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did she ever look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You say when you went to Newmarket for two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When did you go to Newmarket, after your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
After mother died, yes, because the woman wasn't with us then was she. Father - she wasn't with us then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 She was only here when your mother was around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 That
's - that's right, yes, she wasn't here then because the children were getting older then and - I mean - I went away, as I say, I was young myself - and - my sister had her own place didn't she, 'cos she was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So you went away for two years, about 1908 to 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
That's right, yes, and I stayed there for two years with my Uncle Fred. As I say he's got two houses at - Newmarket, but - now he hasn't, he's only got the one, he's on the racecourse. I used to ride around that - racecourse on a li
ttle Shetland pony every morning. I used to have a little Shetland pony and - smashing little thing he was and - if possible the boys that do the horses, you know - in the stables there, I always used to try and get in there to help brush the horses tails
 or plait 'em up. I used to love to plait the tails if they were - long tails you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Had you been there much before you went to live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No, not a lot, no, no, I didn't go a lot be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So this was quite a new experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 It was
 a new experience for me, and great fun. I used to thoroughly enjoy it, and of course I had - I had a nanny there to wait on me and to do everything for me. My Uncle Fred had the servants that used to wait on him and his - Auntie Dolly. 'Cos they were bor
n mostly into a - you see I was born mostly in what you might say to money. In where the money was. So therefore I didn't have to - worry about anything you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would your mother or father make or mend the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Beg pardon? No. No, we
 used to get this woman to do it. Oh no, they never did nothing like that. They'd go and buy a suit - my father would or else mother'd go and buy her dresses. But - regards to doing any mending I think this - woman used to do a little bit of sewing - for 
her. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 But not make clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where would you buy the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well, wherever - nearest to the shop. I think my mother - when she died, she laid - she laid in - Lambs Conduit Street, in Francis the undertakers, and - I c
an quite recollect now that - my father lifted me up, he - she laid in the undertaker's, lifting me up - to look into the coffin to see my mother. And I kissed her and I can quite - remember that quite well. Although I was only seven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Do you remember the actual funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes. Yes, I can remember the funeral, it was pouring as hard of rain - and - Francis buried mother, and she was buried at Finchley. Not in a private grave. Just in an ordinary grave. At least - father wasn't buried with her so I 
should imagine it would have been a - ordinary - grave. And - we came back from the funeral - and - oh I think it was three days after that that my father took me down - by car to Newmarket to see Uncle Fred. But I didn't stay, I came back with daddy, and
 he found it was a bit too much so - as I say I went down there to live for two years. So - I thoroughly enjoyed it, enjoyed life altogether. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was your mother very often ill before she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No, no. She died of - double pneumonia 
- and bronchitis, she caught a chill. Just a sudden death, yes, no, she was - well we used to go to theatres and everything, you know, we used to go in the car to - Drury Lane or - Lyceum or the - Hippodrome and the Holborn Empire and - all the theatres d
own the West End I know, living down there you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When you were very young you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, yes. And these -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of things would you see then then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well - when I was young we used to go to the - there used to be a the
atre in Drury Lane - where we went to the - to see that show this week, called the Old Mo. And it was next door to a public house. And - we used to go by car. And - go and see dramas. The \{BLANK\}
 Seven Day's Leave, on His Majesty's Service, and - my father
 never drank. My mother never drank. And - but - he always used to take - one of the men - that used to mind the shop - with us. He used to like a drink, this - man, so - when we used to come out about twelve o'clock - shows never ended then 'til twelve a
s
 you know, well you wouldn't know but they didn't - and - the pub used to keep open 'til one in the mornings sometimes. My father never used to shut his shop 'til twelve sometimes. And he always used to take this man in this pub next door to the Old Mo th
e
y used to call it, and - used to be a man stand outside this theatre - one of those - carts with baked potatoes, and salt, and he always used to buy me one and then the man used to put the salt on, he used to sit me in the car, while daddy went into the p
ub and had a drink with this man, never used to be in long, and he always used to say to this gentleman with this cart - take - give a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4343885\charrsid683676  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 eye on her will you, won't be gone long, and I used to sit and I used to enjoy this - and a bit of paper, this baked potat
o with the salt on, and - I can remember once I said to my dad - well where's the butter, there's no butter on it. And he said, well you have to forget that, you'll have to forget the butter. But the man was always there. Year in and year out and he alway
s used to be - the show - after mother died - on a Thursday. Those days - was the only day you could close your shop - any hour or any day, but - they used to be open to all hours in the morning - well I know -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What time did he open?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 My father, 
he used to get the men to open - he never opened, he used to get the men to open up for him - say about - six o'clock in the morning. 'Cos he used to have 'em outside as well, immaterial to the fruit being inside, fruit stall was always outside for people
, and - he used to deliver most of his orders - to his customers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would he have to go down to the market initially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, he used to send the men. The men used to go to the market.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would they go to Convent Garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Convent Garden Market, 
yes, 'cos we're not far from there where we lived. Oh yes, I went to Covent Garden Mar - Market many a time with the boys - that used to get the goods, 'cos I used to be asked to be let to go with him, and - it was great fun going to that market. Well at 
t
he moment - there's a friend of mine there that's got a pub, there's a pub there that opens up at - it may be there still now, she may be still there, opens up - three o'clock in the morning. For the mar - men for the market, and then she closes about ele
ven. And - she's got a sister up here and I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Has she got a special licence for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes, for the men for the market. Yes, and I'm sure it's still there now, I haven't been down to see her for - ages. But her sister lives in Drupe Street where I l
ived - moved from - three year ago when I lost my husband, and - I've never asked her if her sister's still there but - she was there a few year ago to my knowledge - about three or four year ago, so I should imagine the pub's still there - it's only just
 for the men for the market, so they can go and have their drink. And she used to open as I say about - two to three in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Do you remember something like that when you were very young as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well - I - no, no, I never knew of that di
d I. I didn't - I remember the place, yes, I can remember going past it, the pub, little tiny pub it is, not a big pub, it's just like - you'd think it was just like a little shop. That's all. Those days. But I can remember it quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How many men did your father have working for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well - I should imagine he had about - there was two in each. That's six.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were these shops all close together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - well, as I say, one was in Jud Street, one was in Red Lion Street and one was in Lambs Conduit Street. So - they're not far apart from one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did he have them all at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh no. As - he shut like one shop to make a bigger shop, he - you see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 He moved from one business to the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, to the other. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did your father work in the shop himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh sometimes, yes, oh - oh yes, he give a hand sometimes, though he was mostly in the - back with mother of course, mostly with my mother. And - sitting down. Used to like a game of ca
rds. Used to get the men come in there and - sometimes play a game of cards. But my mother never believe in 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 She didn't like cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. She didn't like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Why didn't she like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 I - I think she had a - premonition of some kind t
hat - they were unlucky. And - father give 'em up, he wouldn't play. And it seemed a very funny thing that - on the day that my mother died father was playing cards. And my father always said that he think it was the cards that killed her, but of course i
t was just - coincidence that she died, but he never had a pack of cards after in the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What would they think about playing games or cards or anything on a Sunday?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh no. No Sunday - we never used to have that, always used to have to go to c
hurch, three times a day. I used to go down to - I used to go to church in - near Drury Lane, there's a big church there. I used to go there to - early morning mass - church. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Is this the Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, and I used to go in the after
noon, what they used to call Sunday school. And I used to have to go in the evening. And brother - my brother Will and myself was in the choir - singing in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Every week you'd do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you have any choir outings or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No, we never had any choir outings. And underneath the church, they used to have a big hall. We used to go dancing - down there, as youngsters when we - as we got bigger like, and really - good times. So - that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you ever go on things like Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Once. Yes we went to - Hadleigh Woods. And I got lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Over in Kent somewhere I think. I couldn't tell you, I know I got lost, and they were searching for me, and - oh and th
en there was another - time that - we had the - dad had the shop in Ann Court, and mother dressed me up, you know, with these big crinoline bonnets, satin bows and the big dresses that stand out and we were going to Newmarket - to see my Uncle Fred and mo
t
her said to me - well she didn't actually dress me, it was this lady that dressed me, and she said, now, you go and stand and wait outside - 'til we get the car and we'll go down to see Uncle Fred. Well further along the road - the street in Ann Court, th
e
re used to be two little boys there, daddies - one daddy - one of the boy's daddy had a tailor shop, and - name of Jenkins, and - I couldn't tell you what the other one was, anyway I was standing at the door waiting, and they came by and I was - I used to
 
be a little tomboy, I used to like the boys - and they had - we used to - have a little bag at the side of us with your pennies in you know, and of course - I used to always be at the till, daddy's till for pennies for these little boys, and they came by 
a
nd - I suppose one must have been about - eight and the other nine - and asked me where I was going. I said I was going to Newmarket to see my uncle. They said, oh no - don't go there. Let's go down the Thames. 'Cos Thames wasn't far from where we were. L
e
t us go and have a boat - shall we have a boat out? I stood there and mother and father was busy in the back, and I followed up - I followed them. And - we went to the - you had to go down three steps to get the boats, I expect you'll find it if you go al
ong that way, see the steps. Well they used to have what they used to call penny strugglers. That's - if anybody was in difficulties - these boats used to come along and - pick - help pick you up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 These were rowing boats were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, yes. We 
got in this boat and the thing tipped up. And - dear God - I can remember - somebody picking me out the water. I don't know what happened to the other two boys afterwards, and - a gentleman put me in a big car, and a lady, and they took, me to their house
. And - I remember this - these two servants - and when I come to myself I was wrapped up in blankets, and when I come to my - myself, the first thing that was - \{BLANK\}
 Of course they brought me back so - my father's shop after they - got me dried and - ni
ce bath I went in, but wherever I was these dogs would follow me. Gorgeous creatures. And - I went to stroke one, and I was a bit timid, 'cos we did have a dog - dog of our own. And - I can remember - cor this lady - oh - very reserved - very - you know, 
p
osh lady, and - she said - don't be afraid darling, she said, he won't hurt you. And - took me in and give me this bath and dressed me, got me clothes dried and put 'em back on, and - of course while they're fetching me back where I lived, they're out sea
rching for me aren't they. But the other two boys, they got saved all right, they were - quite all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh - not very old, I was about - I say mother died when I was seven, so I could only have been about - six. I could only have been about five or six but I can remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were you told off after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh definitely was, put to bed wasn't I, I never used to - never got a smacking. But my father used to say - bed. And that was enough. And there I had to sta
y 'til he come up. And I can always remember standing in the - outside the bedroom door saying, may I come down now daddy? And he used to say, you'll come down when I tell you, not before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was it your father who did most of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes, he was the - he was the - he was the one that give the orders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of man was he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh lovely. Beautiful man. I haven't got a photograph of him or my mother but - I know my - I think my mother-in-law's got those and - she's - ninety so I've - coul
dn't go and ask her for them. You know, she wouldn't know where they would be, she's still alive, she's ninety as a matter of fact, my husband's mother, but - his word was law, and we had to abide by him and - 'cos those days as you know we used to have t
he dishes all on the table all laid out and - the meat was cut and passed around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Who would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well my father, yes. He used to sit at one end and mother used to sit at the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you have your own set places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes, oh yes, 
we all used to sit at the table, you all knew your own place, grace at table before you ever had any meals, and you always had to ask before you left the table, may I please leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were you taught to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes. Oh yes, the - my father used to teach us that, what side - right side from wrong side and - how to hold your knife and fork, and how to drink your soup - when you pick your soup up, you know, that way, never pick it that way always drink yo
ur soup that way and - drink it from the opposite side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What about things like when you'd leave food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh you always had to leave a bit for manners. Just a small - portion, never - empty your plate, you always used to have to leave -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were you allowed to have second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes. Oh yes, second helpings if you wanted it, if it - as I say, if I'd have been poor of course I wouldn't have been able to have had it would I? But - we were never allowed to - overload yo
urself. My father would - he'd look at you and he - my father say - don't you want any more? And - brother Will and myself, we'd look at one another as much as to say, well we've had enough. I'd say, no, I don't want any more daddy. He'd say, all right. S
ee. Leave the table. Go and wash yourself - wash your hands and - get ready for whatever it is - you're going to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were you ever allowed to bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh we were allowed to - not to allowed to - laden the 
kitchen with anything. We all had our own - we all had our toy room. Room of our own like to play in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When you were allowed to bring toys and books when you were having meals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No, no. No. Never nothing like that, it was very rude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where would you eat, which room would you eat in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well we used to eat in the dining room of course, what we used to call the sitting room. Those days. So - the sitting room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would you eat all the time in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You'd eat every meal in there would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
What would be the routine when you wanted something on the table would you just help yourself to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Or would you ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You'd asked for it to be passed over. We were never allowed to - 
move - over the table, you used to have to allow - to come back, round, brought round and - you know, have to help yourself with it. We was never allowed to stretch across the table, my father would never have that. That's the way I bought my sons up. Nev
er allowed to do things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What was the sort of routine day of meals, what times did you have meals?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well we used to have lunch about twelve. We used to have a late dinner. Lunch would be - say just salad or something like that, but we always had our late dinner, at - six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4343885\charrsid683676 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676  consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Roast beef. Baked potatoes or something like that. Greens or - cabbage. Peas and something like that, and a sweet. And - then - you was allowed an apple. Mother used to allow us an apple because he always said that - apples was good for you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Who would cook the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well we used to have a woman to do that. Cook the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You say she only came in three days a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Well - what happened there - would b
e - perhaps father would go out - he'd want to go out for a day somewhere so therefore if we went out - used to have meals out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 In cafes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How often would you go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh, not very often. Wouldn't be very often, so therefore -
 was - if he knew he wasn't going out he used to get the woman in to change her day - to come and do the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So your mother wouldn't do any cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. My mother never done any cooking. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 It was always this woman who came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, always at the back, yes, she done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What time would breakfast be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh that would be say around about - let me see, nine. Nine. Yes, we all had to be up - my brother and I had to be up and washed - and - 'course I was young a lady used to c
ome in and dress. She used to dress me, yes, do - my frocks up and that and - then she'd go and see to mother, see what mother wanted - or anything, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did your father ever help with things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Like dressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh not dress me, no, oh no, he had nothing to do with that. He used to make, he didn't do it, I used to do it - try and do it myself. But very seldom. Very seldom I ever dressed myself, 'cos I nearly always got something wrong. And that wouldn't be al
l right for dad, you had to be - just spick and span. Everything had to be all right, same as me brother just the same. Everything -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of things did you say your father did help with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well, as I say - he didn't have much to do - at all,
 anything, just his books he used to do, like his - accounts. His books for - customers, the bills and all that, he done most of that. And - as I say as I got older I used to - help a little bit in the shop - with him. Used to get the - orders ready. For 
p
eople. So - otherwise - doing nothing, you know, I used to - when I - as I got older I used to go to dancing, I didn't go to work - until - after I was married - I was married a twelve months, I had the boy. And I didn't work - I didn't work then, I had t
he other son I didn't work. I don't think I - worked for about - oh until they were nearly - old enough for school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Then what kind of work did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - the first work I done was engineering. Machine. On the lay or on the press or on the - you know, all in - engineering works. For aeroplanes or something like that. Used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you ever do an apprenticeship or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No. Never done that, apprenticeship. Who, my father do you mean or myself? No, not me no. I just learnt it myself. See -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were you a member of a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No. Not trade - no, we used to go in to work and - come out of work and then I used to come home and - the children used to be time for the children to come in from school and I us
ed to get somebody to come and fetch them. Go and get them like and - cook their dinners and - just take 'em back to school myself. And I'd fetch 'em myself and then - I only used to do - I didn't used to work all day, I used to do it like part time. Beca
use children need attention. So therefore - I had to be with 'em. Most of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You say you worked again later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes, well I was - after that - what happened after that, engineering, well that was the war wasn't it. War was finished. And - 
then of course I was caretaker at the Synagogue, Jewish Synagogue. I was there ten years - at - Chamberlain Road. That's up near Willesden way. I was caretaker there and I used to do like all the - special days for the catering, Jewish catering and all th
a
t. And as a matter of fact my daughter-in-law was a teacher there, in the Jewish - Kinder, for their little Jewish children. I had a photograph here the other week of where she's sitting teaching the children English and - painting, you know, 'cos they - 
they've taken some English children in now, but she teaches the Jewish children how to paint, read English, and the Jewish teacher teaches them how to - read Jewish, Yiddish and all that, you know, all that kind of talk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 So they have the two together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, she does the two together, yes. Oh yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When you went to Newmarket when you were seven you said you had a nanny?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes, we had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did she teach you anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No. I never - she never taught me anything there until 
I went to school - here. That was at Thanet Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - if I left school - I was fourteen wasn't I. I was fourteen when I went to school. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Do you mean you were fourteen when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Pardon
? I was fourteen when I left school, yes, well I started school when I was about - when I come back from Newmarket so I must have been about nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You didn't go to school until you were nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You didn't go when you were five years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No. No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
I don't know. Father thought I was - had enough intelligence I suppose that I didn't need it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did he ever give you any lessons himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes, at home we used to have books he used to read - s
how us how to read the books and - spelling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Just ordinary - those big books we used to have for the ABC and - you know, all that. And prayers, learn to say your prayers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Beg pardon? No. No, never had that. No. In our family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would you be taught to say prayers before going to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes, every night. And breakfast - and before we had lunch, before we had our breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Who taught you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 My father. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was your mother a Catholic as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No. Only my father. Not my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did your mother ever give you any lessons before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 I thought it was against the law not to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No. I us
ed to get my lessons and I - I usually went with a - well between eight - eight and nine I went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 When you came back from Newmarket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes. When I come back from Newmarket. And I've got - I had a wonderful reference as you see by that, that was excellent. I was a good scholar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You didn't find it difficult to catch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No. No, I went quite normal to school and - I was - well advanced with the other - other kiddies here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What school did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Thanet Street. St Pan
cras. That's where I went, as you see there, teacher's signature and all. And that was - I left in the October didn't I, in 1915. Yes. October 1915. I left.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you enjoy school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh loved school. Never had a day off. I used to never stay away. 
My father wouldn't have allowed anyway. Oh no. We all - school - my boys were the same. Never have a day off of school, more often I used to say to the eldest boy - have a morning off this morning son. No thank you mother, I want to go to school. And they
 
would never - and they were both - well the youngest one won a scholarship. And they never left school 'til they were - sixteen. And - the Army collared 'em when they were eighteen. So therefore I never had no advantage - out of my children for working. W
e
ll then - when they came out of the Army, the eldest boy's in the - he's in the - Post Office. He's the head one - over men. And - he's sat for seven - he's had seven - exams and - can't get no higher. So therefore he's got - he's over the men. And the ot
her one's got his own shop. Television ship. He makes televisions and - you know, radio sets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did you like about school particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Who me? Everything. Really - mm. Liked everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of subjects were they apart from reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Pardon? I used to love composition. Or when we went out or wherever we went I used to love reading, drawing, the only thing I never used to like was geography. That was one lesson I used to try and get out of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you have one teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, we had men. Men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well - a mixed school. Boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was it a religious school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No. Just an ordinary school. Wasn't a religious school at all, just ordinary school. Used to - we used to have the men, we never used to have women. They were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Often they had the class divided didn't they, the boys in one section and girls in another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
That's right. That's right, but - no - no, we didn't, we used to mix, like they do today. We used to mix. Mix.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You were there five years in all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
What kind of things did the teachers try and put over to you do you think, what kind of values?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - if - if there was anything special wanted she'd - they all used to call on me. Be
cause I was intelligent as you see. I - I only got to see a thing or - read a thing, I had it, I've got it. In the mind and - if everything - anything they wanted done as you see reading that, they would pick on me to do it. Very help - and I was a wonder
ful needlewoman. And basket making. I was good in everything - as you can see by the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What were they like on things like punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes, I was always regular there you see that. Never late. I was never -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were they strict about it though,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes, definite, you had to line up in the hall - if you were late. Line up in the hall and have to write out - a word so many times. I must not be late. But I never done that. I never had to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were the children at school from similar homes to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes. Yes. Similar -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 They were roughly the same kind of children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes. Yes. Very - there was - well not to say well to do but comfortable, you know. And then yet there was some poor, but not many. Not many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were there any gangs or anything like that in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. Oh no. No. And from the school - they used to take us to Holborn, used to be a big college - on the corner of Fisher Street, I think it's still there now. And we used to have to go there for dr
awing. And for - on the roof, they used to have a kind of a garden. And we used to have to take a plant and plant and go once a week - on top of the roof, to see how this plant was pro - progressing, see whose was - and whoever's come up first we won a pr
ize of - some little thing. And - I - they used to say that I had green fingers. Like they said here. And mine always used to seem to shoot up the first. 'Cos I loved gardening. I've always had a garden of my own and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you have a garden in Jud Street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Judge Street? Yes. Garden. Beautiful garden we used to have there, glashouse and all. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you ever grow your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No, we never had - mostly flowers. Used to be flowers in there we used to plant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would you have anything like livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Any what? No - no. Well we used to have birds, canaries, mostly canaries and didn't have budgies, we had canaries, my father was very fond of - a canary, and rabbits. And tame mice. Brother used to have a lot of tame mice. 
And I'll tell you what happened. This is real funny. 'Course the times getting on. Real funny. I had - plenty of toys, but there was one special doll. Those days. We used to have big dolls like that. And they used to have wax faces. And stuffed bodies and
 
wax legs - dressed - and - my - my youngest brother - he used to be a - lovely brother he was - and - tantalizing - he always used to try and go and - take one of my special things that I - glorified in to play with, and damage it. And this particular day
 
- father was busy down in the shop like and - I went into my room to get this special doll. Long fair hair, wax face. Was during the winter. And he'd been standing in front of the fire. With the doll and of course you know what wax is don't you? When I we
n
t in he's standing with this doll of course the doll had no faces. Well I went blue murder, I screamed I kicked. And 'course father come running up to find out what was playing on here, I said look what he's done to my dolly. It's got no face. So he said 
-
 oh never mind about it, got more plenty dollies to play with. No, no, look what he's done. Father said, well we'll have to buy you another one. No, I don't want another one, I've - I' - I want me other - me other dolly Well - anyway we got over that diff
i
culty. I thought to meself in me own little way, have me own back on you. So these tame mice - we had a cat, two cats. Went into - the room - in this white cage, I can remember this white cage with all these tame mice. And I opened the door and I let all 
t
he mice out, of course the bat had three or four of 'em. I never forgot that, and the rest of 'em - I put the - left two in the cage and I put the cage on the floor, and of course the mice are running about the floor and I thought it was great fun. But of
 course I did until I see the cat diving after 'em. Did I get punished for that. I got no hiding or nothing like that but I was kept upstairs in my room for about - two hours. Never nothing to eat, my father wouldn't give me nothing to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was it your
 father and your mother or just father who you think gave you your values?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No, father gave the orders. Mother - would never interfere. If my father said a thing it - it went, you had to abide by it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of things do you think he or your m
other as well brought you up to believe were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - be truthful, be honest, and never do any harm to anybody, because she always used to say, if you harm a person - it always comes back on you, she used to tell us. Be kind to one a
nother, love one another, and I was a child that was that - I am here now, they'll tell you here. Never seen such a nice \{BLANK\}
 'cos it's meself I'm praising but they'll tell you it here, they all like me here and - jolly. Always laughing. And - always cracking jokes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of person was your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh lovely woman. Beautiful. And very very very quiet. Very - very select, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did she ever go out much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes, wherever dad went she went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 They went out together as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh yes, yes. We all used to go out together. But if they were going to a theatre - we used to have the - the woman to mind us, brother Will and I and - they'd go out and then - they'd come back and - they'd just pop their - head round t
he corner of the bed to see if everything was OK and then the lady would stay the night. They - 'cos those days the theatres used to keep open 'til - twelve half past twelve. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What time did you have to be in bed in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh, quite early. I used to have to get in bed by six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Who would put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
The lady would. She'd put us to bed. And - oh yes, always six, and my son - my children just the same, I brought them up just the same way. Mater of fact if it was over six when 
they were young - they'd ask to go to bed. They'd ask me. I mean, they wouldn't - they'd go and have their wash and take their - they - both had a room separate 'cos always having a house, and - take their comics and their sweets and - books and go up and
 
read. The reason was that they had a room each was because when - when they used to get in bed they used to fight. When have these - he's got - this little - all the clothes, the other one's got all the clothes and - I'd go in there, I never - never - hit
 hit my children at all. I only used to have to look at them. And Joey would say to Tony - I think we'd better go to bed don't you, mum's mad. I was in a temper. And up they'd go and no more was said, so they used to say, but they knew. Just like -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Ho
w about your own mother and father, if you ever had any worries would you be able to take them to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Beg - oh yes, oh yes, they'd - oh yes, I only wish mother and father had lived, oh they'd have loved 'em. Well - well father didn't - you see - when my children were born, my father was alive. For a year. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 He died about 1924 did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
He must have done mustn't he. Must have done. Well I had - I had my two - my Joey - my eldest son - used to take my eldest son - that one there, yes, I u
sed to take him - to my father - and of course toys were very cheap those days, and he used to send me - in fact I never used to go in a taxi or anything, he used to send me back home - in a taxi - loaded with toys for the children, 'cos dad wasn't short 
of money. You see. And of course the other fellow come along, he never - saw the other chap. 'Cos he died. Only saw the eldest one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What happened to the shops when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well we had to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4343885\charrsid683676 sell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676  them didn't we dear, we had to sell - give '
em up. You see because - you couldn't trust the men and so we give them up. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Swearing. No swearing in our place. Thought that was terrible. My father and mother never swore. Never drank. No. Never a bad word out of my mother and father, never. Oh no. That was - oh that was well against - rules and regulations. Bad language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How would you say they expected you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well to respect them of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How would they expect you to behave towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well - well we - never used to fight or nothing. We used to have a disagreement, but that was soon settled - by my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you help each other, your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh yes. Yes, oh well - no my b
rothers loved me, being the youngest like of the two and - oh I had everything I wanted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of things would they do for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh they - they'd say - take - make me out for a walk or something like that. And - when - my brothers were never
 allowed to buy me anything out. Were never allowed to - have - like sweets and that in between meals. That's one thing my father never would let us have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Did you ever have pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Oh - well we used to have - go to the - help ourself - we'
d say to my father, can we have so and so? He's say, well - go to the till, put it down on a bit of paper what you've taken. But I never used to put it down all. I used to take more than necessary. I used to take money in a little bag and at school, and -
 
at school - we used to have these - satchels, I show you a photo going to school on me back, and I nearly always used to fill it up with fruit, and - and spending money - I used to - supply the girls and boys at school with it all 'cos I always used to wa
y
 lay me and sweets. And - as I say, we were never allowed to - overdo it or anything like that. I know - I roughed it more - well not what you call rough it if you know what I mean - had my hard times, times when I was short of money when I got married. A
l
though - my husband done seven years apprenticeship - 'cos he wasn't for papers, his was for medical - doctors of Harly Street - birth control and - teeth and - all that, that's how he come to get out of the Army, because he - governor kept writing up - t
o get him out, 'cos he was a - my husband was a key man, he was machine minder, you see, and - they used to - let him off, 'cos he passed Al for the Airforce, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 During the second world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Second world war, yes, that was. Oh yes, but - 
my own life was really a happy one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
What would your parents say you should do if another child hurt you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Beg pardon? Well used to - I just - I used to go home and - say - somebody - hit me or somebody }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10500712\charrsid683676 pu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 nched me or something like that
 and my father used to look me, he'd say - that's quite all right. That's quite all right, that'll be all right. He never used to fuss over me or nothing, no, he said, quite - that'll go. And perhaps sometimes I'd show him you know if we'd been in a bit o
f
 a scrap. Which I very very seldom did. I wasn't a child like that. I was very reserved and very quiet. Not as you might say quiet but - I knew - what to do, I knew how to behave myself, I was never brought out of class for bad behaviour, as you can see i
n that. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 You don't remember being punished at all by the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Never. Never. Never had a black mark against my name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What would happen to other children if they were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Beg pardon? Well they'd be put in a corner with a - hat on top of their head.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 A dunces cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes. Or they'd be - stay behind and have to write - two hundred lines - I must not do this and I must not do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Can you remember anyone being on their at this school you went to, who were always on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No. No. We all used to mix. Oh very seldom there used to be any - disagreements of any kind. We were children that - were brought up in the right manner and - knew how to behave themselves. Very very seldom you see any fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would you play with them in the playground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Oh definite, yes, oh yes. If they had a game and they wanted me in it I'd play in it, no matter what it was. But if I found it was a bit - rough - you know what boys are - jumping over backs, that's a th
ing I would never do. I was always taught never to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What kind of things did you play then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Well we used to play hopscotch, marbles, what they used to call - all fours like with the - squares and the buttons. What's name and the - shuttlecocks - all that kind of thing and - there used to be yo-yo's those days. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How about hula hoops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes, and - those hoops you put round you know and - skipping ropes and - 'course we went to gymanastic a lot of - lot - quite a lot at school - the horses and all that, what they - what do they call it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Gymkhana?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. Used to do a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Where would you do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Well we'd do that in the drill - what they used to call the drill room.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 That was nearby the school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Yes, in the school. That was in the school itself. Downstairs. Oh yes, that was all in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Was there any children that your parents didn't want you to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No. No, they would never suggest that. They used to say that e
ach child was equal the same. No matter what. They would say - perhaps someone might come in to my daddy or mummy, dirty frock or something like that - my father'd look at me, he'd say, what was that you said? Dirty frock? That doesn't make any difference
 my dear the same as you. Same as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
No. No. Mustn't - used to be that - a dress on - and - well when you say - not allowed - if it was accident, perhaps you'd slip over or something like that, that w
as excused. But to come home mucky, you want to know why, what you've been eating, how you've come home mucky, you've been eating in between meals. So therefore - I knew that I - wouldn't do it, no. I wouldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 What did your parents think you should do when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
Stay quiet. We should sit - sit down, you mustn't inter - interrupt either. You mustn't dare - they were talking and you interrupted that would be a punishment, you'd be sent upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Would you say that you 
received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or was one more important than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 No, both parents. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 There's one or two things I'd like to clarify.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Yes. As long as it's over by one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 Could you remem
ber how old approximately your mother and father were when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 
How old? Oh God, how old they - you got to go back, I was seven when she died I'm seventy-one this September. Quite young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7892935 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 How old was she when she died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9010046 LW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13049666\charrsid683676 I think sh
e was in her forties. She must have been mustn't she? 'Cos she was married in - 1900, wasn't she. And I was seven when she died. So - well you can soon - soon go back from there.
