d white patent - high legged boots. They used to be one and eleven those days, Jackmans in Drury Lane. That's what I was telling you about, there used to be the theatre there I used to go to, the Old Mo, and - my father used to get on the phone and order 
a
 pair and he'd - send a man along and fit, 'cos those days they didn't used to - fit your foot like they do today, there was never nothing like that, they'd just get a pair of shoes and put them on to your size, and - that was that. They used to be one an
d
 eleven. And pinafores we used to wear, father used to get them in Drury Lane, not Drury Lane, Leather Lane, all frills, you'd get one sixpence ha'penny they used to be - those day - six - sixpence ha'penny and tuppence ha'penny for socks. And yes - a dre
ss - for a dress it used to - they used to be - a shilling. A beautiful dress, frills.
